poisoned by his wife, <LOCATION>Agrippina</LOCATION>.
   In <DATE>1775</DATE>, the <ORGANIZATION>United States Navy</ORGANIZATION> began as the <ORGANIZATION>Continental
Congress</ORGANIZATION> ordered the construction of a naval fleet.
   In <DATE>1843</DATE>, the Jewish organization B'nai B'rith was founded in <LOCATION>New
York</LOCATION>.
   In <DATE>1845</DATE>, <LOCATION>Texas</LOCATION> ratified a state constitution.
   In <DATE>1943</DATE>, <LOCATION>Italy</LOCATION> declared war on <LOCATION>Germany</LOCATION>, its one-time Axis
partner.
   In <DATE>1960</DATE>, 30 years ago, the third presidential campaign debate
was broadcast, with Republican nominee <PERSON>Richard M. Nixon</PERSON> in
<LOCATION>Hollywood</LOCATION> and Democrat <PERSON>John F. Kennedy</PERSON> in <LOCATION>New York</LOCATION>.
